The Nigerian Film Corporation (NFC) has said it will expand and strengthen its operations through robust partnerships and collaborations to ensure growth of the industry. Dr. Chidia Maduekwe, the NFC Managing Director said this in a press statement in Jos. He said the NFC has mapped out various strategies to tackle the challenges and impediments to the growth of the film industry in 2020 and beyond, and noted that “the strategies includes robust NFC stakeholders’ engagement which is intended to secure their commitment to achieve the needed success, training and retraining opportunities for film makers.  NFC parleys filmmakers in Kano NEXIM bank announces co-production funding at Cannes Film Festival Gov. Ikpeazu promises N10m for films shot in Abia